From: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Date: Thu, 26 Jul 2018 15:06:10 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] efi: Allow efi=runtime
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/wagi/linux-stable-rt.git
Git-commit: afb1da8271a0bfa8f7ae48e02a129c56620d4256
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository
References: SLE Realtime Extension

In case the option "efi=noruntime" is default at built-time, the user
could overwrite its sate by `efi=runtime' and allow it again.

Acked-by: Ard Biesheuvel <ard.biesheuvel@linaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Wagner <dwagner@suse.de>
---
 drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c
+++ b/drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c
@@ -104,6 +104,9 @@ static int __init parse_efi_cmdline(char
 	if (parse_option_str(str, "noruntime"))
 		disable_runtime = true;
 
+	if (parse_option_str(str, "runtime"))
+		disable_runtime = false;
+
 	if (parse_option_str(str, "nosoftreserve"))
 		set_bit(EFI_MEM_NO_SOFT_RESERVE, &efi.flags);
 
